\n<Chelsea>You've grown so much♥ But remember, if you do something bad,
big sis will come to defeat you!

\n<Chelsea>Next time, let me hear the story of your adventures! I'll
tell you about my adventures too. But that'll be way in the
future, so wait for it!

\n<Chelsea>\n[1], you're short but you have big boobs, huh. Just like
my little sibling should be. All the women in the Catfield
family are like that.

\n<Chelsea>\n[1], are you studying hard? I'm sorry, it seems like I'm
the only one who gets to be free. Both of us are expected to
do well...

\n<Chelsea>The Cat Borrowing Hand is said to be the hand of our
ancestors! It's amazing that they lend us a hand from the
other world. \n[1], you had mom's hand, right?

\n<Chelsea>So whose hand is the Louisham? I don't know, maybe
grandma's? I heard grandma was also a beauty.

\n<Chelsea>So whose hand is the Wanzwarth? I don't know, maybe
grandma's? I heard grandma was also a beauty.

\n<Chelsea>I wonder if the day will come when we fight together. Well,
I think I'd probably win by a landslide. It'd be pitiful to
beat you up too much though.

\n<Chelsea>The Cat Borrowing Hand is a secret technique passed down
through the Catfield family. I couldn't use it at all and I
don't have magical power, but I do have physical strength.
Whatever that means.

\n<Chelsea>I'm on an adventure with a hero for various reasons! Shion
is really flimsy and unreliable, but strong! That's why I'm
sticking with him. I want to win someday!

\n<Chelsea>Have you cleared Challenge Mode? You only get a small
weapon, but it's fun to fight with a handicap!

\n<Chelsea>Is grandpa doing well? I heard he used to be quite strong.
Apparently, he had a completely new fighting style that
combined swordsmanship and boomerangs.

\n<Chelsea>It must have been tough fighting succubi since they're
always doing lewd things, right? When your dick gets hard,
it seems like it would be hard to move.

\n<Chelsea>This room is called "Ikuukan?" or "Clear Baya" as some say.
What the heck is that!

I haven't seen Ending 2 yet... To achieve it, you must have
maximum Karma (by not making any wrong choices). To save
Mare.
Would you like to see a hint?

To save Mare, you need the "White Vial." You can obtain the
White Vial during the "Bijou-1st battle" by not hitting the
treasure chest even once.

To use the White Vial, you must know what's inside. You can
learn how to use it by "reading a book" during the
investigation of the ancient ruins in the "Bijou-1st
battle."

If you "have the White Vial" and "know how to use it," you
can save Mare by defeating her in the "second battle" and
resisting her temptation.
カルマを最大にする方法

The basic rule is not to succumb to temptation. You must
defeat the succubus. However, the correct choice is to
succumb to temptation only in "Radro's second battle" (the
text will also be in blue).

If you cut down Mare, your Karma will still increase, but
you will no longer meet the conditions for the ending.

Ending 2 "Phantom Thieves Kittens". Karma is at its best.
Cleared after saving Mele.

The slums were half-destroyed, but we succeeded in repelling
the monsters. The cat borrower can no longer be used, but we
should be fine without borrowing anyone's help now.

However, having been taught the tricks of thievery by Radlo,
the Kittens continue to steal for the sake of the children
in the orphanage to this day. Until the day when Drine and
Lumare can join hands.
\n<Moo>What business do you have with me?

\n<Moo>I do enjoy a good chat. Ask away. I know everything. Some
even call me a walking library. Though that's a lie.

\n<Moo>Coagulation crystals were born long ago during a conflict
known as the Elemental War, a crystallization of "blood,
malice, and hatred" that naturally solidified. Most of them
have been obtained by the Demon King or already disposed of
by humans.

\n<Moo>However, like the recent disturbances, there's a chance some
were sealed away and hidden, or left in places no one can
find. We must find and dispose of them before the demons do.

\n<Moo>Malice is the emotion that monsters favor most and it is
also the source of their existence. That's why they attack
humans. Simple, isn't it?

\n<Moo>In ancient times, humans were broadly divided into four
types: the Fire Folk, the Water Folk, the Wind Folk, and the
Thunder Folk. Their conflict was known as the Elemental War.

\n<Moo>You have inherited a strong lineage of both Fire and Wind
Folk. The mixing of elements signifies that they have
reconciled with each other.

\n<Moo>You seem to be able to use magic of different elements with
ease, but normally that would be incredibly difficult. Only
a select few geniuses and heroes can perform such feats.

\n<Moo>To put it simply, it's about whether your ancestors were
apes or something else. And usually, the offspring of
beastfolk and humans tend to be human. If interbreeding
continues, the number of beastfolk will likely decrease.

\n<Moo>The Catfield family has been uniting beastfolk to prevent
their numbers from dwindling too much. You all must
understand this best.

\n<Moo>A while back, they weren't treated very well, but now it's
normal to treat beastfolk the same as humans. Your ancestors
worked hard for this to become the norm.

\n<Moo>Don't do anything to tarnish your family's name, alright?
Chelsea. I'm speaking to you.
\n<Chelsea>Why are you suddenly throwing this at me?

\n<Moo>Hmm. Well, your head isn't exactly good. To be frank, it's
quite bad. I apologize, but it wouldn't be wrong to call you
a fool.

\n<Moo>When we first met, you were knocking down adventurers left
and right. You caused so much trouble that there was even a
subjugation request issued for you. It seems you just
couldn't help wanting to test your overwhelming power.

\n<Moo>I suggested you fight monsters instead of people, which is
why I recommended you become an adventurer. And that's how
you ended up sticking with us.

\n<Moo>You're a hotheaded, impulsive bruiser with a straightforward
nature, not a bad person at all. Somehow, you have this
strange charisma about you. In the end, you get along with
everyone.

\n<Moo>At heart, you're kind and warm-hearted. Your cheerfulness
has helped both Shion... and myself. That's the kind of girl
you are.
\n<Chelsea>(I feel like I've been praised a lot. Ehehehe♥)

\n<Moo>(I should end on a compliment... That was close, I almost
went on a tirade. Being too honest is one of my faults.)

\n<Moo>Me? I am the Holy Dragon Bahamut. Moo is fine. It'll make
you feel more attached, won't it? But let me make it clear,
I'm nothing like a Pomeranian.

\n<Moo>Well... if I had to say... I'm something like Shion's...
guardian.

\n<Moo>Shion? Well, we'll get to that eventually. All will be
revealed in time.
